<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Well, it was announced yesterday that UO2 is no longer being produced. There's a <A HREF="http://www.avault.com/news/displaynews.asp?story=3212001-16245" TARGET=_blank>story</A> located on AVault about it. I personally think this is a sad, sad thing. I'll be the first to say that I wasn't a big fan of the original UO, but the new one looked like it was going to clear up all the issues I had with the original and be a really deep RPG that I thought I'd enjoy. I feel a sadness I feel when that much originality and creativity goes bye-bye, like when FASA closed their doors. There's one less world for us all to enjoy together...<P>------------------<BR>Muse<BR>Bard and Cartographer<p>[This message has been edited by Muse (edited 03-22-2001).]
