<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Its amazing how similiar your stories sound to my own.<P>I started playing UO in beta, but I chose to leave a year ago.  I became tired of the constant changes with no warning, of the lack of in-game support.  And though I missed my friends (I did give them all my houses, money, etc), I have found EQ to be refreshing.  If I was to participate in PvP, I may do so on one of the several servers.  But if I want to role play, or just adventure knowing that I'm at least safe from death at another player's hands should I choose, I can do so.<P>I find the EQ players much more into roleplaying, friendlier, and more apt to help you when you need it.  Must the graphics in EQ are outstanding.. <P>Plus, although I enjoyed the houses, pets, and whatnot, I did become very tired of having to "refresh" them.. or to pay someone to if I went on vacation... <P>Llua Musical<BR>Bard and Adventuress
